    passage: "RIDGEFIELD DENTAL PRACTICE\nPatient Information — Post-Extraction Care Guide\n\nThank you for attending Ridgefield Dental Practice. Please follow these instructions carefully after your tooth extraction to support healing and avoid complications.\n\nFIRST 24 HOURS\n• Bite firmly on the gauze pad for at least 45 minutes. Replace if saturated.\n• Avoid rinsing, spitting, or using a straw. These actions can dislodge the blood clot and cause dry socket.\n• Apply an ice pack (20 minutes on, 20 minutes off) to reduce swelling.\n• Take prescribed pain relief as directed.\n\nFOLLOWING DAYS\n• Rinse gently with warm salt water from 24 hours onwards (half a teaspoon of salt in a glass of warm water).\n• Avoid smoking for at least 72 hours, as this significantly increases the risk of dry socket.\n• Eat soft foods and avoid the extraction site for 48 hours.\n\nWHEN TO SEEK URGENT CARE\nContact us immediately if you experience severe or worsening pain after 48 hours, heavy bleeding that does not slow with pressure, or signs of infection such as fever or swelling that worsens after 3 days.\n\nFor non-urgent queries: (03) 9901 4422 | ridgefielddentalcare.com.au",
    passageTitle: null, type: "single",
    questions: [
      { id:"xp7-s27a", part:7, question:"Why should patients avoid using a straw in the first 24 hours?", options:["It can cause pain at the extraction site","It may loosen the gauze pad","It can dislodge the blood clot and cause dry socket","It increases swelling"], answer:2, explanation:"'These actions can dislodge the blood clot and cause dry socket.'" },
      { id:"xp7-s27b", part:7, question:"When can patients begin salt water rinsing?", options:["Immediately after the extraction","After 12 hours","After 24 hours","After 48 hours"], answer:2, explanation:"'Rinse gently with warm salt water from 24 hours onwards.'" },
      { id:"xp7-s27c", part:7, question:"For how long should patients avoid smoking?", options:["For 24 hours","For at least 48 hours","For at least 72 hours","For one week"], answer:2, explanation:"'Avoid smoking for at least 72 hours.'" },
      { id:"xp7-s27d", part:7, question:"Which symptom requires immediate contact with the practice?", options:["Mild discomfort on the first day","Light bleeding in the first hour","Swelling that worsens after 3 days","Slight tenderness when eating"], answer:2, explanation:"'Swelling that worsens after 3 days' is listed as a reason to seek urgent care." }
    ]
