    passage: "[Document 1 – Memo]\n\nTo: All Production Staff\nFrom: Quality Assurance Manager, Stefan Novak\nDate: October 5\n\nI am writing to notify all production staff of a quality control concern identified during last week's batch audit.\n\nDuring testing of Batch 77-C (manufactured September 29–October 1), three units were found to have substandard adhesive bonding in the product casing. While the affected units were isolated before dispatch, the incident highlights a need to review the adhesive application step in our production sequence.\n\nEffective Monday, all line supervisors must conduct a visual check of adhesive application at the end of each production cycle, in addition to the existing end-of-line quality gate.\n\nA root cause analysis is currently underway. Results and any further procedural changes will be communicated by October 18.\n\nPlease direct any questions to the QA team at qa@novexmfg.com.\n\n[Document 2 – Supervisor Email]\n\nFrom: Priya Mehta <p.mehta@novexmfg.com>\nTo: Stefan Novak <s.novak@novexmfg.com>\nDate: October 7\n\nDear Stefan,\n\nThank you for the memo. I wanted to clarify a few points before implementing the new check on my line.\n\nFirst, should the visual check be documented in the existing QA log or in a separate record? Second, if a supervisor identifies a bonding issue mid-cycle, should production be paused or should we continue and flag the affected units for review?\n\nFinally, I noticed the memo says the root cause analysis will be complete by October 18. Will line supervisors receive a briefing before that date, or should we wait for the full report?\n\nThank you,\nPriya Mehta\nSupervisor, Line 4",
