    passage: "[Document 1 – Donor Recognition Event Invitation]\n\nBLUEHORIZON FOUNDATION\nAnnual Donor Appreciation Dinner\n\nDate:   Friday, November 15\nTime:   7:00 p.m. for 7:30 p.m.\nVenue:  The Pavilion Rooftop, 280 Harbour Drive\n\nDear Friend of BlueHorizon Foundation,\n\nYou are warmly invited to our Annual Donor Appreciation Dinner, an evening dedicated to celebrating your generosity and sharing the impact of your support over the past year.\n\nHighlights of the evening include:\n• A programme update from our Executive Director\n• Video presentations from three project communities in Southeast Asia\n• Recognition of our Platinum Donors (cumulative giving of AUD 50,000 or more)\n• A keynote address from Ambassador Sarah Lindt, United Nations Resident Coordinator\n\nDress code: Business formal\nRSVP by November 8 to events@bluehorizonfdn.org\nDietary requirements should be advised at time of RSVP.\n\nSeating is limited; early RSVP is appreciated.\n\n[Document 2 – Attendee RSVP Email]\n\nFrom: Dr. James Osei <j.osei@oseifamily.org>\nTo: events@bluehorizonfdn.org\nDate: November 4\n\nDear BlueHorizon Events Team,\n\nThank you for the invitation. I am delighted to confirm my attendance at the Annual Donor Appreciation Dinner on November 15.\n\nI would like to bring my wife, Helen, as my guest. Could you please advise whether a guest ticket is available, and if so, whether there is an associated cost?\n\nRegarding dietary requirements: Helen is lactose intolerant. My own dietary requirements are none.\n\nI should also mention that I may be slightly late — I have a board meeting finishing at 7:15 p.m. that evening. Would it be possible to hold a seat for me?\n\nBest regards,\nDr. James Osei",
