    passage: "[Document 1 – Product Brochure]\n\nPRIMECHARGE PRO SOLAR POWER STATION\nModel: PCP-2000 | By SunCore Energy\n\nPower your life off-grid with the PrimeCharge Pro — a portable, high-capacity solar power station built for outdoor enthusiasts and emergency preparedness.\n\nSPECIFICATIONS:\n• Battery capacity: 2,016 Wh (lithium iron phosphate)\n• AC output: 4 x 240V outlets (total 2,000W continuous, 4,000W surge)\n• Charging: Solar (up to 700W input), AC wall, or car port\n• Full charge via AC wall outlet: approximately 2.5 hours\n• Full charge via solar: 3–5 hours (weather dependent)\n• Weight: 18.5 kg\n• Warranty: 5 years on battery, 2 years on components\n\nRETAIL PRICE: AUD 2,499\nFree shipping on orders over AUD 500.\n\n[Document 2 – Online Review]\n\nPosted by: DesertTrekker_AU | 4 out of 5 stars\nDate: February 12\n\nI purchased the PrimeCharge Pro PCP-2000 for a five-day camping trip in outback South Australia. Overall I'm very impressed — it powered my fridge, lighting, and phone charging throughout the trip without any issues.\n\nCharging via the included 200W solar panel took around 7–8 hours under clear skies, which is longer than the brochure suggests, but I only had the single panel. I assume two panels would bring that closer to the spec.\n\nThe unit is heavy at 18.5 kg, but it came with a carry handle and a wheeled trolley, which made transport manageable.\n\nMy one complaint: the AC outlets don't have covers, so sand and dust got inside during the trip. Not a major issue, but worth noting for outback travel.\n\nWould recommend for serious campers and as a home backup.",
