    passage: "[Document 1 – Notification of Renovation Works]\n\nTo: All Tenants, Pacific Trade Plaza\nFrom: Property Management\nDate: September 2\nRe: Level 1 Common Area Renovation — September 16 to October 10\n\nWe wish to advise all tenants that the Level 1 common area — including the lobby, lifts, and amenities — will be under renovation from September 16 to October 10.\n\nDuring this period:\n• The main lobby entrance will be closed. All tenants and visitors must use the Clarence Street side entrance.\n• Two of the four lifts will be operational. Expect delays during peak hours.\n• The café on Level 1 will remain open but will operate with a reduced menu.\n\nFor deliveries and large item movements, please contact building management to arrange supervised access on weekdays between 7:00 and 8:30 a.m.\n\nFull access will be restored by October 11.\n\n[Document 2 – Tenant Email]\n\nFrom: Sandra Lo <s.lo@brightspark.com.au>\nTo: management@pacifictradeplaza.com.au>\nDate: September 10\n\nDear Management,\n\nThank you for the notice regarding the upcoming renovation. We have two questions.\n\nFirst, we have a large furniture delivery scheduled for September 19. We would like to arrange supervised access on that day. Could you advise whether the 7:00–8:30 a.m. window is the only available time, or whether other arrangements can be made?\n\nSecond, our office is on Level 1 and we frequently receive clients. Can you confirm whether the Clarence Street entrance is fully accessible and well signposted for first-time visitors?\n\nThank you,\nSandra Lo\nOperations Manager, BrightSpark\n\n[Document 3 – Management Reply]\n\nFrom: Property Management <management@pacifictradeplaza.com.au>\nTo: Sandra Lo <s.lo@brightspark.com.au>\nDate: September 11\n\nDear Ms. Lo,\n\nThank you for your email.\n\nRegarding the delivery on September 19: the 7:00–8:30 a.m. weekday window is our standard supervised access period during the renovation. However, we can accommodate a one-off arrangement after 5:00 p.m. on weekdays if the morning window is not suitable. Please let us know your preference.\n\nRegarding the Clarence Street entrance: it is fully step-free and accessible. Temporary signage has been installed at the original main entrance and at street level to direct visitors to the Clarence Street door. We are happy to provide a brief orientation map upon request.\n\nPlease don't hesitate to reach out if you have further questions.\n\nPacific Trade Plaza Property Management",
