    passage: "[Document 1 – Product Listing]\n\nLUMINEX PRO WIRELESS EARBUDS\nModel: LP-7 | SoundStream Audio\n\nExperience studio-quality sound in a lightweight, truly wireless package.\n\nFEATURES:\n• Active Noise Cancellation (ANC) with 4 adaptive mics\n• 10-hour playback per charge; up to 40 hours total with charging case\n• IPX5 water resistance\n• Multipoint pairing: connect to 2 devices simultaneously\n• Wireless charging case (also compatible with USB-C)\n• Available in: Midnight Black, Arctic White, Forest Green\n\nPRICE: USD 199\nWARRANTY: 1 year (earbuds); 6 months (charging case)\n\n[Document 2 – Customer Review]\n\nRating: 3/5 stars\nReviewer: QuietCityListener\nDate: May 5\n\nI bought the LP-7 in Arctic White two months ago for commuting. The sound quality is genuinely excellent for the price — warm bass and clear highs. The ANC is decent but not best-in-class.\n\nThe issue I've had is with multipoint pairing. Switching between my laptop and phone is clunky — it often requires manually disconnecting from one device before the other reconnects. This seems like a firmware issue that should be fixable.\n\nBattery life has been fine — I get about 9 hours per charge, which is slightly under the advertised 10.\n\nI contacted support about the multipoint issue and was told a firmware update is planned for late Q2.\n\n[Document 3 – Brand Response]\n\nPosted by SoundStream Audio | May 7\n\nThank you for your detailed review. We're glad the sound quality is meeting your expectations.\n\nWe acknowledge the multipoint switching behaviour you've described. Our engineering team has identified the cause and a firmware update resolving this issue will be released in the Week of June 16. The update will be delivered automatically via the SoundStream app.\n\nRegarding battery life: some variance from the rated 10-hour figure is expected depending on volume level and ANC usage. Your 9-hour result is within normal range.\n\nWe appreciate your patience and hope the firmware update delivers the seamless switching experience you're looking for.\n\nSoundStream Audio Support",
