    passage: "[Document 1 – Staff Handbook Extract]\n\nGRIEVANCE PROCEDURE\nLodestar Financial Services\n\nLodestar Financial Services is committed to resolving workplace grievances promptly and fairly.\n\nSTEP 1: INFORMAL RESOLUTION\nEmployees are encouraged to raise concerns with their direct manager in the first instance. Where this is not possible or appropriate (e.g., the grievance involves the manager), the matter may be raised with the HR Business Partner directly.\n\nSTEP 2: FORMAL GRIEVANCE\nIf the matter is not resolved informally, the employee may submit a written grievance to the HR Department. The grievance must clearly describe the issue, relevant dates, and any supporting information.\n\nSTEP 3: INVESTIGATION\nHR will acknowledge the formal grievance within 3 business days and will complete an investigation within 20 business days. The employee will be notified in writing of the outcome.\n\nSTEP 4: APPEAL\nIf the employee is not satisfied with the outcome, they may appeal to the Chief People Officer within 10 business days. The decision of the Chief People Officer is final and binding.\n\n[Document 2 – Employee Grievance Email]\n\nFrom: Ryan Nkosi <r.nkosi@lodestarfinancial.com>\nTo: hr@lodestarfinancial.com\nDate: November 4\n\nDear HR Team,\n\nI am submitting this email as a formal grievance under the company's Grievance Procedure.\n\nOn October 15, I was passed over for a promotion that was given to a colleague with less experience and fewer performance results than myself. I raised this informally with my line manager, Anthony Prescott, on October 17, but was told the decision was final and no further explanation was provided.\n\nI believe the promotion decision was not conducted in accordance with the company's stated promotion criteria, and I am requesting a formal review.\n\nPlease acknowledge receipt of this grievance at your earliest convenience.\n\nRyan Nkosi\n\n[Document 3 – HR Acknowledgement]\n\nFrom: HR Department <hr@lodestarfinancial.com>\nTo: Ryan Nkosi <r.nkosi@lodestarfinancial.com>\nDate: November 6\n\nDear Mr. Nkosi,\n\nThank you for submitting your formal grievance on November 4. This email confirms receipt of your grievance in accordance with Step 2 of our Grievance Procedure.\n\nAs outlined in the procedure, our investigation will be completed within 20 business days of this acknowledgement, with a written outcome communicated to you by December 3.\n\nAn independent HR investigator has been assigned to your case. You may be contacted to provide additional information during the investigation.\n\nYour grievance will be treated in the strictest confidence.\n\nHR Department, Lodestar Financial Services",
