    passage: "[Document 1 – Award Nomination Form Summary]\n\nREGIONAL SMALL BUSINESS EXCELLENCE AWARDS\nNomination Summary — Category: Innovation in Service Delivery\n\nNominee: Bloom Floristry Studio\nNominated by: Eastfield Business Improvement District\nContact: Maya Tanaka, Owner | m.tanaka@bloomfloristystudio.com\n\nBusiness Description: Bloom Floristry Studio is a boutique floristry business established in 2019, based in Eastfield. The business employs 6 full-time and 3 part-time staff.\n\nNomination Summary: Bloom Floristry Studio was nominated for its development of a proprietary subscription delivery system, BloomBox, which matches customers with seasonal flower arrangements tailored to their colour and style preferences, using a brief online profile created at signup. The system has achieved a 94% customer retention rate since launch.\n\n[Document 2 – Judging Panel Notes]\n\nCandidate: Bloom Floristry Studio\nEvaluating Judge: Patricia Lim, Chief Innovation Officer, Greenfield Ventures\n\nStrengths:\n• Genuinely innovative use of customer preference profiling in a traditionally low-tech sector\n• Strong retention data (94%) validates the commercial effectiveness of the concept\n• Scalable model — the subscription system could be licensed to other floristry businesses\n\nAreas to explore:\n• How does the business manage seasonal supply constraints while honouring customer preferences?\n• Is there patent or IP protection on the BloomBox algorithm?\n\n[Document 3 – Award Shortlist Notification]\n\nFrom: Regional Small Business Excellence Awards <awards@rsbea.org.au>\nTo: Maya Tanaka <m.tanaka@bloomfloristystudio.com>\nDate: October 1\n\nDear Ms. Tanaka,\n\nWe are delighted to inform you that Bloom Floristry Studio has been shortlisted as a finalist in the Innovation in Service Delivery category of the Regional Small Business Excellence Awards.\n\nThe Awards Dinner will be held on Saturday, November 2, at the Grand Pavilion Hotel. Please confirm your attendance (up to 4 guests) by October 18.\n\nFinalists will be invited to present a 5-minute overview of their innovation at the dinner before the award is announced. Presentation guidelines will be emailed to you by October 10.\n\nCongratulations on this recognition.\n\nAwards Secretariat",
