    passage: "[Document 1 – Product Recall Notice]\n\nSAFETY RECALL — CLEARPATH BABY STROLLER MODEL CP-550\nIssued by: Clearpath Juvenile Products\nDate: July 20\n\nClearpath Juvenile Products is recalling the CP-550 Baby Stroller (all colour variants, manufactured January 2023 – April 2024).\n\nHazard: The front wheel locking mechanism may fail under load, causing the stroller to roll unexpectedly, posing a fall risk to the occupant.\n\nSerial numbers affected: CP550-10000 to CP550-87500\n\nCustomer Instructions:\nStop using the product immediately. Register at clearpathrecall.com to receive a free repair kit. Alternatively, customers may choose a full refund by returning the unit to the original point of purchase.\n\n[Document 2 – Retailer Email]\n\nFrom: Jessica Ho <j.ho@babyworldstores.com.au>\nTo: recalls@clearpathproducts.com\nDate: July 22\n\nDear Clearpath Recall Team,\n\nWe are a retailer that sold the CP-550 through 12 of our stores. We have an estimated 180 units in customers' hands from the recalled batch. We have already begun contacting affected customers via email and in-store signage.\n\nI have two questions:\n1. Can customers return units directly to our stores for a refund, rather than going through the recall website?\n2. Will Clearpath reimburse us for the cost of processing these returns and any associated labour costs?\n\n[Document 3 – Clearpath Response]\n\nFrom: Recall Coordination Team <recalls@clearpathproducts.com>\nTo: Jessica Ho <j.ho@babyworldstores.com.au>\nDate: July 23\n\nDear Ms. Ho,\n\nThank you for your proactive communication to your customers — this is exactly the response we had hoped to see from retail partners.\n\nIn response to your questions:\n\n1. Yes, customers may return units to your stores. Please process these as standard returns and submit them to our logistics partner, ReSolve Freight, for collection. Collection kits with pre-paid shipping labels will be dispatched to all participating retailers by July 28.\n\n2. Clearpath will reimburse retailers for direct labour costs associated with processing recall returns at a flat rate of AUD 15 per unit returned. Submit a reconciliation report to recalls@clearpathproducts.com by August 31 to receive payment.\n\nThank you for your partnership.\nClearpath Recall Coordination Team",
